title: For Sale/Trade:  WW2 Star 1911
postcontent: I am the second owner of this Soviet captured Star Model B 1911 9mm made in 1943. The gun has custom “firewood” grips and comes with 1 magazine. It takes down exactly like a 1911. It was manufactured in 1943 and certain parts of the firearm are stained red from Russian cosmoline such as the extractor, the contact piece between the slide spring and barrel, and the trigger has a very light red tint to it. The finish is around 75% due to some holster wear but is still pretty good for a firearm that is 74 years old and has been possessed by both the Spanish and Russian armies. I field stripped it recently to clean it and it was in great condition. It was blued at the Star factory and when the Russians captured it, it was dunked into cosmolene. After who knows how long, it was turned over to a dealer who then reblued it and sold it on the civilian market to the 1st owner. All stamps are still intact and look great! This is a great collectors item. Stars that can be bought today are generally from the 70-90s era so WW2 models are not nearly as common so that is why the pricing is different. This particular pistol has a story behind it due to a eagle holding a swatztika on the grip. The original dealer who had a crate of stars knew that some stars were sold to the nazis during the war. So he attempted to sell mine as Nazi owned due to the selling price of originals being 3-4 times the price of a normal WW2 Star. It’s a pretty cool conversation piece even if it is a fake!The last picture, the Ñ, is the Spanish proofmark for 1943. Beside it is the verification stamp placed by the proofhouse in Spain. Star has an official website and they show all the dates for every proofmark ever stamped on a Star product. All numbers match. If you are knowledgeable about the Model B you will know that they are known for stovepiping, this is not a range master it is a safe queen that will accrue in value.This is a great piece for Spanish collectors or just someone who wants a WW2 1911! I can send additional pictures of the inside, bore, and what not. If you have any questions just ask! I do not ship and I would be more than happy to send pictures of the bore upon request! Price is firm
